# Pre-commit quality gates

**Before creating any commit**, run the checks that CI will run. Do not rely on partial checks (e.g. typecheck alone).

From repo root:

```bash
bash scripts/ci/run-pr-quality.sh
```

This mirrors the PR **Typecheck & lint** job:

1. `npm ci`
2. `npx tsc --noEmit -p scripts/ci/tsconfig.typecheck.json` (sdk + signaling **sources**, not workspace dist)
3. `npm run lint` (eslint — catches unused imports, `import type`, etc.)

### When to run

| Changed paths | Required before commit |
|---------------|------------------------|
| `packages/sdk/`, `packages/signaling/`, `examples/`, `scripts/ci/`, `.github/`, `eslint*`, `tsconfig*` | **`run-pr-quality.sh`** |
| `packages/bindings/` (`.rs` or `index.d.ts`) | **`run-pr-quality.sh`** + rebuild bindings if TS surface changed |
| `crates/` only (Rust) | `cargo test` for affected crates; run **`run-pr-quality.sh`** if any TS or workflow files also changed |

### Common mistakes

- **`npm run typecheck` is not enough** — it typechecks workspaces/examples but does not run eslint. CI fails on lint even when typecheck passes.
- **Do not skip lint** because a local typecheck succeeded.

### Before push / PR

Re-run `bash scripts/ci/run-pr-quality.sh` if the last commit touched TS/JS or CI config. For native changes, also run `bash scripts/ci/run-pr-integration.sh` when feasible (needs Linux `.node` or Docker — see `scripts/ci/README.md`).
